003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the street, or more accurately, the alley, the Stealth House appears more like an art installation than a residence. Its corrugated weathered steel exterior is striking: raw, rust-toned, and windowless. But this isn’t just a design choice. It’s a strategy of privacy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWithout windows or fences, the house redefines boundaries. There’s no need for blinds or hedges. The steel cladding forms a clean perimeter that’s both architectural and philosophical, a modern fortress that embraces minimalism while inviting curiosity.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1178\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/modern-house-corrugated-steel-facade-210525-709-02.jpg\" alt=\"A bold mix of industrial and refined materials, this modern home pairs rusted corrugated steel with a shimmering mosaic wall for a striking first impression. The narrow window offers a glimpse into the tranquil, glass-lined interior.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/modern-house-corrugated-steel-facade-210525-709-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/modern-house-corrugated-steel-facade-210525-709-02-940x577.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/modern-house-corrugated-steel-facade-210525-709-02-800x491.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/modern-house-corrugated-steel-facade-210525-709-02-768x471.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/modern-house-corrugated-steel-facade-210525-709-02-1536x942.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1245\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/modern-house-corrugated-steel-facade-210525-709-03.jpg\" alt=\"A bold mix of industrial and re